description: Kotaro Takamiya creates a robot with an extremely powerful A.I. and is taken captive by the Machine Empire. In order to save him, his brother Teppei must awaken the legendary B'T, X. Together they battle their way into the Machine Empire to rescue Kotaro against impossible odds.
name: Vol. 1

description: Continuing their quest to rescue Kotaro, Teppei and X face off against Foh Rafine--one of the four Spirit Generals of the malevolent Machine Empire--and his mighty mechanical B'T. X must quickly recover from spending the last few years dead or Rafine will return the mighty mechanoid to the junk heap...permanently! Meanwhile, Kotaro learns why he was kidnapped by the Machine Empire...and why his freedom could doom them all!
name: Vol. 2

description: Teppei and X have faced many dangers and fought many foes in their journey to rescue Teppei's brother. Now, they must tackle their toughest opponent yet--each other! Caught in Camilla's illusion, the duo must battle to the death...with friends like these, who needs enemies?!
name: Vol. 3

description: Teppei continues his battle with the Shinigami and is nearly defeated. Even worse, Teppei's pride is shattered when Foh tells him that his skills are inferior and that he will die in due time unless he improves them. Meanwhile, Kotaro has incurred the wrath of Misha, has been thrust into Under Hell, from whence no man returns.
name: Vol. 4

description: Bouncing Back from a B'T-ing! Teppei and X have been on the receiving end of a few good beatings recently, but they are by no means down for the count. Fully healed, repaired, and working as a team, they're out to prove that two heads are better then one. But will two heads be enough when they come face to face with their next opponent, a hydra like B'T with nine heads?!!?
name: Vol. 5

description: Strutting to a Brand-New B'T Teppei and X are caught between a rock and a hard place when they face Mislim and the stone-eyed gaze of his menacing B'T. The situation becomes grave when the daring duo are turned into sand! Will a ray of hope shine on our heroes before they're washed away for all eternity?
name: Vol. 6

description: Friends to Foh As the traveling trio of Hokuto, Teppei, and Foh come face-to-face with the army of Quatro, Foh orders his companions to the next point while he deals with this current foe. Although Hokuto and Teppei agree to Foh's request, Teppei soon learns that Quatro and Foh used to be best buds. What will happen when these friends fight?
name: Vol. 7

description: Un-Foh-given When former friends lock in mortal combat, it's do or die for Foh and Quatro! Battered and bruised from Quatro's attack, Foh may not be able to last much longer. When he receives a call from Teppei admitting that he has some sins to confess, Foh decides to risk everything on one final move. All the while Teppei is having his own troubles as he faces off with the nightmarish Maim!
name: Vol. 8

description: I'm B't Teppei doesn't know what to do when Maim appears and sends him into a deep sleep. In this dream world Teppei sees Kotaro chopping the heads off of young women. When Teppei tries to stop him he is stabbed in the chest. Hokuto has been monitoring Teppei's vital signs and sees that his heart has stopped. If Teppei can't find a way out of this nightmare he'll face the big sleep.
name: Vol. 9

description: Could this be the end for Karen? The battle continues in mid-air while back in prison, Kotaro is rounding up the others to plot an escape from Raphaello, but how? Teppei and Foh come upon their 10th Point in the Area, Serome. Something is not right...something has changed them and it definitely isn't for the better!
name: Vol. 10

description: As Teppei, Foh and Hokuto attack one another under Salome's mind control, we get a glimpse into the Dancing Princess' devastating childhood. But while our heroes duke it out, another adversary appears on the scene: Juggler, whose kill total is climbing and whose bloodthirsty eyes are on Teppei and company!
name: Vol. 11

description: Kalayaan is a Philippine comicbook superhero created by Gio Paredes.

There's a surprise in this comic, first there's the story called 'Rude Awakening' -Rocketing into a Twenty-Fifth Century world of genetically engineered warriors, vicious space pirates and greedy corporate overlords, Buck Rogers the last hope of a dying Earth- and then there's the board game called 'The Gauntlet' complete with rules of play and cardboard board and chips.
name: Rude Awakening

description: For most of the past of Budd Roots Cavewoman comic and its titular heroine, Meriem Cooper, the main attraction has been its good-girl art and sometimes naughty humor and action. This one-shot goes a little beyond risqu to raunchy, as Meriem graces each short adventure and pinup either half-naked or totally naked. The special also features Frank Cho characters (and one sketch) along with Roots perception on a assortment of other heroes, heroines, and monsters.
name: Cavewoman Meets The Grandson Of Khong
Strictly for the Birds; Frozen Feud; The Ugly Duckling; Horsing Around; Star Billing; Slack Season
Phantom of the Soap Opera; Trick or Treat?; Woodchopper's Ball; Pottsylvanian Pitch; A Dog's Life; Bat-Ball Batty

volume.name: The Extraordinary Works of Alan Moore

description:
There's a mysterious past buried in the mind of the affable, yet somehow incredibly dangerous Vash the Stampede, and everyone on this desert planet seems to know about it. Not only that, they've been trying to hunt him down for the sixty million double-dollar bounty on his head. Well, enter two insurance adjuster ladies, claiming that the man is a localized disaster, and voile! No more bounty. But that doesn't seem to end Wash's troubles, or his trail of destruction.

This is the world of Trigun. Chock full of hi-jinks, frantic action, dusty wester poses, and a resounding theme: Peace and Love! Join us as Vash continues his adventures across this kooky, unfortunate landscape, seeking something to end his tragicomic journey.

Dark Horse continues its parade of new manga with the second, super-fat volume of Trigun! Set in some kind of post-apocalypse western future, Trigun continues to knit a goofy yet mysterious story about a nice-guy gunslinger with a dangerous past and a huge bounty on his head. Everyone is after Vash the Stampede, but no one can put a bullet in him. Adding to the comedy is the pair of ladies working for an insurance company who must put a stop to Vashs destruction, though they certainly dont believe this amiable prankster is the vicious destroyer. Its a fun read, and super thick, packed full of silliness and action.

name: Volume Two
